AB  - Welfare-maximizing and revenue-maximizing export taxes are compared to three types of profit-maximizing export marketing boards. (A) a board that cannot price discriminate between domestic and foreign customers, (B) a board that can discriminate, and (C) a board constrained by domestic marginal-cost pricing. Adopting a ‘mini-max’ attitude, the policy ranking is shown to be (1) welfare-maximizing tax, (2) board type (C), (3) free trade, (4) revenue-maximizing tax and (5) board types (A) and (B).
