AB  - The literature on public finance has so far completely ignored the question of unemployment. In this paper, the traditional two sector model of tax incidence is utilized to develop a model in which the effect of various taxes can be analyzed and compared. On the basis of this model, we have compared and studied the effect on employment of various equal-yield and equal-rate taxes. Also, on the basis of reasonable empirical assumptions certain policy conclusions are stated.
